node.text:
Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Push the right-hand crown of the incredible BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon and the engine comes to life – the crankshaft turns and the 16 pistons pump up and down, just like BUGATTI’S iconic W16 engine. Two “turbochargers” on the side of the engine block spin while the engine runs, adding to the visual impact.
Incredible to see and unbelievably complicated to realize (the movement is comprised of 578 components), the BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon timepiece seamlessly marries engines and watches – something no other watchmaker has done before.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

Now with the face of Marlon Brando, the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater uses two hammers to strike exposed circular gongs to sound out the hours, the quarters of hours, and the minutes. In the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater, the gongs circle above the dial, visible through the large sapphire crystal and rose gold case. This voluminous case enhances the clarity, tone, and richness of the sound of the gongs.

In the world of watchmaking, the presence of a tourbillon in a watch’s movement places the piece among the elite. @JacobandCo’s Twin Turbo Furious 300+ sets itself apart from this rarified group, incorporating two accelerated triple axis tourbillons into its striking design. The tourbillons work to compensate for the effects of gravity on the precision of the movement.⠀ ⠀
⠀
Even the case of the Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti 300+ is super complicated – made of forged carbon, with a titanium core to ensure water resistance - the case alone is comprised of 88 parts. The grand complication movement is made up of 832 individual parts – incredible to consider that many parts coming together, and amazing to see in action.⠀

node.text: The Astronomia Ruby and Diamond Baguette timepiece features the constantly in motion Astronomia four-arm vertical movement with its four exclusive and always moving complications. For this model, the movement and complications float across a deep red backdrop created with 257 baguette rubies. A 50mm 18k rose gold and sapphire crystal case provides a full view of the movement, complications, and ruby base. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: The 18K rose gold case, the sparkling diamond lugs, and red ruby base, provide a proper balance of color and brilliance for the Astronomia Ruby and Diamond Baguette timepiece. The size of the 50mm case still manages to be comfortable on the wrist while the domed top and side apertures made of sapphire crystal provide a full view of the exposed Astronomia four-arm vertical movement with its four exclusive complications. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: The 18k rose gold and sapphire crystal case of the Astronomia Ruby and Diamond Baguette has open-worked lugs containing 80 baguette diamonds totaling more than six carats. It provides a clear view of the exposed Astronomia movement and its four exclusive complications: a triple axis tourbillon, a rotating magnesium blue-lacquered globe of the earth, a rotating 1-carat spherical diamond with the Jacob Cut, and an hours and minutes subdial with the patented system that keeps the time display at the 12/6 o’clock position throughout the movement’s 10-minute rotation over a base of baguette rubies. #jacobandco #jaconandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: The Twin Turbo features two triple-axis tourbillons, the most complicated, technically most challenging and visually most encapsulating among all tourbillons. The two tourbillons rotate at speeds of 40 seconds three minutes and eight minutes, along the three axes of rotation for a stunning visual impact. The tourbillons, along with the decimal minute repeater and the timing functions are powered by the exclusive manual winding JCFM01 caliber, which is clearly seen through sapphire crystal covers on the front and back of the watch. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: The Twin Turbo combines the exhilarating energy experienced in the world's fastest automobiles with the unparalleled refinement and mechanical complexity only present in the universe of ultra-high-end watchmaking. It’s the first watch to combine two triple-axis tourbillons and a decimal minute-repeater. Powering this high-performance watch is the exclusive Jacob&Co. manual winding JCFM01 caliber. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: The Opera Godfather Minute Repeater has been a finalist in the Mechanical Exception category of the prestigious Grand Prix d’Horlogerie de Genève. This unique timepiece is driven by the exclusive Jacob & Co manual winding JCFM07 movement. It powers the minute repeater, the two-cone, two-cylinder music box that plays the Godfather theme and the triple-axis tourbillon, while maintaining an impressive 44-hour power reserve. The dial also contains the Godfather logo on an 18K rose gold plate and a black lacquered piano with a stylized iconic image of Marlon Brando as Don Corleone. @gphg_official #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #gphg2021

node.text: The Jacob & Co. Opera Godfather Minute Repeater has already disrupted the watch industry with its novel collection of complications and artistic flourishes.
